Web app: user quarantine

Purpose: quarantine/remediate risky/compromised users. This should be a very small app, but security needs to strong.

Back-end Operations:
    Active Directory: disable username(s) and/or reset password to "xxxxxxxxxx"
	Google Workspace: suspend username(s) and/or reset sign-in cookies
	Entra ID: revoke all sign-in sessions for the affected username(s)
    Operation email alerts
    Log all operations to a database 

Front-end: 
    Operator inputs a username or a csv file of users to be quarantined
    App displays username(s) in the table with disable and reset password options
    "Not found" is displayed If a username doesn't exist in AD
    A log search page for admins/operators

    